  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "Which of the following statements regarding the layers of the digestive tract is incorrect?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "The mucosa is the first layer of the digestive tract."
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "The submucosa is absent in the gallbladder."
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "The muscularis propria is present throughout the GIT."
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "The esophagus lacks the submucosal layer."
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer:D) The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6a729a105a169277718788389dbeab\">esophagus</span> lacks the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7cb424e4921692777199f9951be2ce\">submucosal</span> layer</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p>The GIT is histologically made up of 4 layers:</p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>Mucosa</li>\n\t<li>Submucosa: Absent in Gallbladder</li>\n\t<li>Muscularis Propria</li>\n\t<li>Serosa: Absent in esophagus</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"David G.King, Southern Ilinois University\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"NA\" data-source=\"https://histology.siu.edu/erg/GI005b.htm\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"312\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/v3jhIqAXfd4IN9hiUgJE1737608346.png\" width=\"500\" /></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"DrJanaOfficial \" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY 4.0\" data-source=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esophagus#/media/File:Histology_of_Esophagus.svg\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"289\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/LLiqTYlRM5c09K3btItf1737608360.png\" width=\"500\" /></p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [
        "https://image.prepladder.com/content/v3jhIqAXfd4IN9hiUgJE1737608346.png"
      ],
      "explanation_audio_eng": "https://image.prepladder.com/content/My6PIN244H63ZYJ53CLH1750694021.mp3",
      "explanation_audio_hin": "https://image.prepladder.com/content/9Nl5uzLv2ZPWzrOOjSUM1750694068.mp3"
    },
    {
      "text": "A 58-year-old male presents with chronic heartburn and regurgitation. Upper endoscopy reveals the presence of Barrett's esophagus. What is the primary cellular change seen in this condition?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Metaplasia of squamous epithelium"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Dysplasia of squamous epithelium"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Hyperplasia of columnar epithelium"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Hypertrophy of columnar epithelium"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer:A) </strong>Metaplasia of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5be0ee4ea316927771997104326685\">squamous</span> epithelium</p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation :</strong></p>\n\n<p>The primary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12a6f23332169277718402ca6703e2\">cellular</span> change seen in Barrett's <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"84f4cb0ade16927771940b83eacc37\">oesophagus</span> is <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cb4dfcbab11692777192d282b3be7a\">metaplasia</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5be0ee4ea316927771997104326685\">squamous</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53782f88d31692777187177cb73b24\">epithelium</span> into intestinal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8ff554096316927771851cc310435e\">columnar epithelium</span> because of acid reflux/GERD.</p>\n\n<p>Intestinal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8ff554096316927771851cc310435e\">columnar epithelium</span> has <strong>goblet cells</strong>, which are filled with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3a983e569716927771805ed22b90d7\">acidic</span> mucin. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3a983e569716927771805ed22b90d7\">Acidic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7d30ef9aee16927771936bdac2c1ff\">mucin</span> is stained by the <strong>Alcian blue stain</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>Metaplasia is 100% reversible. So this <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cb4dfcbab11692777192d282b3be7a\">metaplasia</span> can be reversed if GERD is controlled with the help of drugs.</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>If GERD is not controlled, then it can lead to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"362992dbb11692777180f9017fc04d\">adenocarcinoma</span> of esophagus.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Barrett_s esophagus Histopathology Labelled\" data-author=\"Mikael Haggstrom\" data-hash=\"723\" data-license=\"CC0 1.0\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Histopathology_of_Barrett's_esophagus,_original.jpg\" data-tags=\"January2025\" height=\"346\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/9jpLCq1rlfmBFFrU95Ga1736862271.png\" width=\"600\" /></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Barret_s esophagus-\" data-author=\"NA\" data-hash=\"724\" data-license=\"NA\" data-source=\"NA\" data-tags=\"January2025\" height=\"510\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/TOe2owIh7kV0sRLoGkIM1736862565.png\" width=\"350\" /></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Barret_s  esophagus-\" data-author=\"NA\" data-hash=\"725\" data-license=\"NA\" data-source=\"NA\" data-tags=\"January2025\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/sPQOvc3pZHlNejN8yvbg1736862659.png\" width=\"500\" /></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>",
