    {
      "text": "A 50-year-old male presents with chronic heartburn for two years. An endoscopy is performed, and the biopsy of the esophageal specimen stained with special stain is shown below. Which of the following conditions is the patient at an increased risk of?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Squamous cell carcinoma"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Adenocarcinoma"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Plummer Vinson syndrome"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "MALToma"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer:B) </strong>Adenocarcinoma</p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p>The above scenario and an image showing goblet cells within the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8ff554096316927771851cc310435e\">columnar epithelium</span> suggest Barret’s esophagus, which puts the patient at an increased risk of <strong>adenocarcinoma of the esophagus</strong>.</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Microscopically, the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5be0ee4ea316927771997104326685\">squamous</span> layer is replaced with<strong> intestinal-type <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cb4dfcbab11692777192d282b3be7a\">metaplasia</span> </strong>containing goblet cells.</li>\n\t<li>Goblet cells are <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"552e9ef8811692777186997018b858\">diagnostic</span> of Barrett <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6a729a105a169277718788389dbeab\">esophagus</span> and have distinct <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"26080f047a169277719334625cadef\">mucous</span> vacuoles that <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b29a1a16ab1692777199ede1c6e28b\">stain</span> blue with <strong>Alcian blue</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"\"><img alt=\"Barrett_s esophagus Histopathology Unlabelled\" data-author=\"NA\" data-hash=\"726\" data-license=\"Open access- Public domain\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Barrett's_mucosa,_higher_magnification,_Alcian_blue_stain.jpg\" data-tags=\"January2025\" height=\"359\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/YGEAsYFMq2FlUUqElS011736863147.png\" width=\"500\" /></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Esophageal disease progression:</strong></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Matsui, Daisuke & Omstead, Ashten & Kosovec, Juliann & Komatsu, Yoshihiro & Lloyd, Emily & Raphael, Hailey & Kelly, Ronan & Zaidi, Ali & Jobe, Blair.\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY NC ND 4.0\" data-source=\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/HE-staining-of-esophageal-disease-progression-10-A-Normal-rat-esophagus-B_fig1_319878013\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"4167\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/8wMF0jG1RrACFpOeloiC1737608752.png\" width=\"4167\" /></p>\n\n<p>A: Normal esophagus; B: Esophagitis; C: BE with goblet cells; D: Dysplasia; E: EAC. EAC: Esophageal adenocarcinoma; BE: Barrett's esophagus.</p>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [
        "https://image.prepladder.com/notes/YGEAsYFMq2FlUUqElS011736863147.png"
      ],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [
