    {
      "text": "A 45-year-old male presents with complaints of severe odynophagia, retrosternal chest pain, and difficulty in swallowing solids and liquids for the past week. He has a history of untreated HIV infection with a CD4 count of 80 cells/mm³. An upper gastrointestinal endoscopy image is shown below. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "CMV esophagitis"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "HSV esophagitis"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Eosinophilic esophagitis"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Candida esophagitis"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: D) Candida esophagitis</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation</strong></p>\n\n<p>The clinical scenario and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a9e7c4b7051692777187a218b539d7\">endoscopy</span> showing curd-like plaques suggest Candida esophagitis.</p>\n\n<p>Candida <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d764404051692777187f6ce218779\">esophagitis</span> is an <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5204097a961692777194904909b6fe\">opportunistic</span> infection seen in immunocompromised individuals (e.g., HIV/AIDS, cancer patients, long-term <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a3e96d80e9169277718551158bbcd4\">corticosteroid</span> therapy or long-term <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c3c986cd721692777189b473814b2e\">immunosuppressive</span> therapy)</p>\n\n<p><strong>CMV <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d764404051692777187f6ce218779\">esophagitis</span> (Option A): </strong>Shallow, linear, or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7ab35d64bd16927771981c8135b442\">serpiginous</span> ulcers on endoscopy.</p>\n\n<p><strong>HSV <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d764404051692777187f6ce218779\">esophagitis</span> (Option B): </strong>Punched-out ulcers on endoscopy</p>\n\n<p><strong>Eosinophilic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d764404051692777187f6ce218779\">esophagitis</span> (Option C): </strong> Seen in patients with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"aa1288c36b16927771814fa5aa84eb\">allergy</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e641c01c4e1692777182943f64af6d\">atopy</span> but not associated with immunodeficiency.</p>",
      "question_images": [
